page.title: 01FOUR OAKS GENERAL
page.content: The area is North of Birmingham and incorporates the northern boundary of Sutton Park, an open amenity area of about 2400 acres.The Park is one of the best natural wild life regions in the Midlands. Most of the area is administered by the City of Birmingham District Council. Urban development is extensive around the Park. Much house building has taken place since 1945 with private development being the most obvious.The type of housing ranges from expensive, exclusive large dwellings in the South East and North West with upper and middle range property apparent everywhere. Detached houses predominate. Social activities are plentiful in this essentially dormitory area.The people are socially conscious and are ambitious for themselves and families.Most people think it a pleasant place to live in.
